Description: Clipboard manager and emoji picker for GNOME on Wayland
 clipd is a frosted command palette for clipboard history and emoji search.
 One hotkey opens a Raycast-style picker; tabs switch between clipboard
 history and a Unicode 16 emoji catalog (~3,800 entries).
 .
 Features:
  * Clipboard history — text, URLs, hex colors, JSON, code, images
  * Unicode 16 emoji search with fuzzy name / alias / shortcode ranking
  * Pin / unpin clips (24-hour TTL on unpinned, pinned clips persist)
  * Auto-paste via ydotool (Ctrl+V) or super paste (Ctrl+Shift+V)
  * Per-row context menu: Pin, Paste, Super paste, Delete
  * GNOME Shell extension for continuous background capture
 .
 After installation, three one-time steps:
  * Start the user daemon:  systemctl --user enable --now clipd.service
  * Enable the extension:   gnome-extensions enable clipd@devtochukwu
  * Bind a hotkey to /usr/bin/clipd-pick (Ctrl+Alt+V is the suggested default)
